These are the some of the rules for snort, you can try it.
alert icmp any any -> $HOME_NET any (msg:"ICMP Test"; sid:1000001; rev:1;)
alert tcp any any -> $HOME_NET 21 (msg:"FTP Coneection"; sid:1000002; rev:1;)
alert tcp 192.168.110.172 any -> 45.77.210.251 any (msg:"Tata Strive"; sid:1000003; rev:1;)
reject tcp 192.168.110.172 any -> 45.77.210.251 any (msg:"Tatastrive dropped"; sid:1000005; rev:1;)
log icmp $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET any (msg:"ICMP Message";sid:1000001;rev:1)

To test above rules, you can used following command (give your configuration file path):
snort -T i eth0 -c /etc/snort/test_snort.conf  

To run above rules, you can used following command (give your configuration file path):
snort -A console -q -i eth0 -c /etc/snort/test_snort.conf



